caption: Nice place, friendly staff.
The food was amazing.

This place is so good!! The food here is excellent, great price and they have  friendly staff .The line is long but worth it according to my brother. Every time I have eaten from here I get Post-mates which saves me the hassle of standing and waiting in line.
I love this place, great food & service. Really nothing but good experiences here.

Due to COVID, breakfast options were limited around the loop. Potbelly had temporary hours and didn't open until 9. I was getting a late start so it worked. I had a sausage, egg and cheese sandwich and a coffee. The coffee was fresh. The sandwich was good and hot. Hearty portions for breakfast.  They were keeping the dining area very clean. The spacing was comfortable.
Friendly and efficient employees, they take your order and  quickly you have a fresh sandwich or salad to enjoy there or take with you to go.
The morning crew is so lively and very nice and friendly!
Friendly staff, quick service, great sandwiches (both for breakfast and for lunch).
Love potbellys. Wreck on multi grain.

I see lots of positive reviews so maybe our experience was a fluke...my wife and I were the only two in the shop when we arrived, and it took the staff about five minutes to even start making our sandwiches. They were friendly enough, just slow and inattentive. They were out of turkey so we had to change our order, and the soda machine was out of both coke and iced tea. The sandwiches were good enough, so hopefully we just caught them on an off day.
Another great experience with the always pleasant staff.

This is by far my favorite Potbelly location in the city. The employees here are actually friendly and the food is always good. This location has a great atmosphere and I enjoy sitting in here to eat my food.
People working there were very excited. Made the experience better, otherwise, a typical Potbelly with typical taste
Great food...
Great chicken pot pie soup
Food was very good, the place is very busy but there is always a place to sit and chill.!!!!

There had to be some reason that I keep coming back every lunch.  It is just a sandwich shop!  Is it something in the bread?  Maybe some addictive substance in the meat?  I just don't know!  I will have to keep coming back until I solve this.
Great sandwiches

The good way awesome, however the service was too slow, only two customers other theen me and my friend, and we still had to wait over thirty minutes,, or was with the wait and the SOUP WAS TO DIE FOR...MMMMMM
Ridiculous food at ridiculous price.
Speedy service and quality food

I was visiting out of the city, this is the worst potbelly I've ever visited, I am used to have orders handled in 1 minute AT MOST, other potbellies have a 4-5 people at a time handling all orders,here you have 2 guys doing everything,  the guy getting my condiments ignored/forgot the soup in my order(instructed by his partner), when I reminded him, it was like I have never asked for it. on my visit same guy taking my order was the one preparing one, good luck if someone is ordering 10 sandwiches an you're the one behind. I ordered what it was going to be a take out for several people, I was not offered a bag or anything, provided a spoon for my soup. Also maybe I am spoiled from midwest politeness, but this staff has the classic I-hate-my-job attitude. the 2 stars are because the sandwiches were good, ever I am coming back to Chicago I sure will skip this place. Or maybe I am in the wrong side, and I should learn big city food places are expected to have very low customer service quality.
Great first time there, lady met us and explained it all. Ordered her recommendation and it was great.

The feel of the restaurant is nice and warm, you feel comfortable sitting in while you eat. The sandwiches on the menu are delicious and no two are alike. You can also add other toppings on your sandwich then what it already comes with. The variety of soups is pretty good too. The service was fast and the workers were very nice. 4/5 stars would visit again
(Translated by Google) Rich!  (Original) Rico!
The best
Great sandwich at relatively reasonable prices. Great staff!
Long line but once they got orders booked ahead in line went a lot faster.
Great go to for lunch
Love the salads and friendly staff
Potbelly standard fare.  Plenty of seating though.
Friendly staff.
Love just about all there sandwiches.
Great service and fast . 👍👍👍
Good pulled pork sandwich.

Potbellys was right outside our hotel and we ate there several times for breakfast and lunch.  Their milkshakes and cookies were great too. The price of food was very reasonable compared to other places. Would definately go back.
Staff was rude but the sandwich was delicious
Really good sandwich :)

If you’re looking for an alternative for all the unhealthy food downtown this is definitely a great choice. Way different feel then subway and your other sandwich choices. Don’t get me wrong they have things on their menu that will add to your calories, but they definitely have a multitude of healthier choices for the average consumer.
Plenty of seats, nicely decorated. Staff could be more friendly...

I've been here a couple times now and have had a pleasant experience each time. Both times have been online orders and my sandwich was ready at the advertised time and tasted delicious. The employees are extremely friendly and made me feel like a valued customer.
Chocolate shakes here are amazing!

Big Potbelly fan and this one is closest to my office. I usually order same thing (turkey on wheat with no cheese). I would say 50% of the time, it comes out with cheese and then I have to wait for new one to be made. Not sure if this is issue with the iPad/order taker, the sandwich maker or just the system. Other than that, delicious.

Same great food. Some of the staff could be a little more engaged with customers. Employee in front of me in line was ordering her own food for lunch. She was talking on her iPad (I do not mean iPhone) while ordering and holding up the line. Lots of seating and convenient location.

Not very impressed. They ran out of enchilada soup by 1:00 on a Saturday. The employees did not smile once. Lastly, we ordered the Italian and felt a bit jipped. There was not much meat. We could have gotten a foot long at Subway for $6 when we paid more than that for a 6inch here with very little meat.
This Potbelly recently had a makeover and it looks GREAT!

Of the Potbelly's in the area, this is not one of my favorites. It's a bit cramped in the line area, and often smoke from the ovens fills the space. Seating is quite plentiful, and the adjoining Rookery Building is a nice view from some spots. The food is as standard as any other Potbelly, which is good, but the overall experience just isn't as nice.
Best place to eat. Fast service. Nice place to eat and hangout for a bit.

my experience today was wonderful at this location. first of all, I LOVE Potbelly's food, but ive found that not every shop has the same service and atmosphere. this shop blew me away how well they are run. i got through the line very quickly. everyone was friendly. they got my order right, rung up quickly, and there was no extra time for my warm sandwich to cool down too much. i am very very satisfied and I would love to make this my new shop, especially since it's so close to my job. great job, guys!

They ran out of chicken ran out of broccoli soup. Order a pickle the guy who got the order threw it at the cashier fell and hit the floor then she had the nerve to ask me if I still wanted it. It really sucks because I'm a frequent customer but o well there is plenty of other places to eat in the area.
nice
Great meeting spot for coworker meeting.  Located in the busy loop, be prepared to wait.  The ingredients that are used for the salads and sandwiches are always fresh.

I love the Wreck salad, it's really filling meat and cheese combo. Potbelly's is very reasonably priced, fresh and filling. So many sub combos I try different ones everytime and really like the roast beef and chicken salad.
